      <head>Adolf Schustermann</head>
      <div>
        <!-- BODY: -->
        <p><hi rend="bold">Adolf Schustermann</hi>,  Berlin directory publisher and newspaper information agency (Adressenverlag und Zeitungsnachrichten-B&#xFC;ro), founded in 1898, which Schenker, who called Schustermann his "Berlin Observator" (OJ 1/14, p. 506, January 11, 1914), used to scan Berlin newspapers for Schenker-related items and send him clippings.  Schustermann is recorded also as providing material for Paul Bekker.</p>
        <p>There was also an Austrian publisher of the name Adolf Schustermann (1861-1935), who may perhaps have been connected with the Berlin company.</p>
